descriptionMarkdown:
### This is a Rail Block system for Nauvis in Space Age. It's designed around easy scalability from early to late game and low stock levels (buffered items are not productive). It also works well on Vulcanus once you have cliff explosives.

##### New: If a station is empty, partially filled trains are also dispatched. No more waiting for full trains of blue chips.

It is designed around 1-2 trains and modules with up to 8 Inputs/Outputs. Train stations are designed without buffer chests and with one waiting bay. With 2 trains for every input station and 1 train for every output station this should allow for gap hopping of the trains based on supply and demand. At the beginning some trains need to be send manually to input stations, because not all trains can go to output stations after building. This should no longer happen as soon as enough gaps are available. Because train ghosts do not trigger rail signals, it is also advised to disconnect a module from the network until everything is built (I remove one rail segment at entry and exit of each station).

Periodicity of a small block is 76 tiles.

It contains blocks for Tier0, Tier1 - T3, some beta Blocks for T4 (Vulcanus-Tech) and an T5 example for debug mode. 

A mod can be used to easily use rate calculator for the whole base: 
https://mods.factorio.com/mod/RailBlockHubRateCalcRecipes?from=updated

I felt I had to improve my previous blueprints due to the changed boundary conditions of Space Age, specifically the later access to cliff explosives and the smaller late game blueprints.

This is still work in progress.

It uses:
- https://factorioprints.com/view/-OBl_0jTgBW6EQ8uDWTv
- smelters and T5 Demo module based on: https://www.youtube.com/@Zeroster_Guides

Changelog
- v0.2: improved symmetry.
- v0.3: added mixed belt unloading and debug demonstrator
- v0.4: Furnace optimizations, test of new base grid
- v1.0 (Apr 25): First version of all T1 modules.
- v2.3 (Apr 25): T0-T1 with partial dispatching. This reduces negative buffer effects.
- v2.4,2.5: Bugfix
- v2.6: Changes to dispatching method, bugfixes and Improvements (e. g. module block). T2 modules added.
- v2.10 (May 25): T3 Blocks added. Beta test of first few T4 Vulcanos Blocks.
- v2.11 Works well on Vulcanos as well
